comments: This was interesting, and very well paid for the time it took. Thank you!
Thank you! I enjoyed being a part of this study it was interesting!
No comments or issues.  Very well done study.
the directions could have elaborated about the answers more
Tough to determine moral behavior when compared to fair behavior.

I really hope you don't think I didn't consider these scenarios carefully, but they all seemed fair, even with the power imbalances. In the case of the one where John volunteered to babysit even though the other guy (Caleb?) had more influence. John volunteered though.
I enjoyed being a part of this study!

I wish we could be more precise with the ratings. Sometimes I felt like what exactly I was rating was unclear. For example, with the poor family giving an expensive gift to the rich family, I don't think it's morally forbidden for the poor family to give the gift, but I do think it would be more morally forbidden for the rich family to accept the gift.
It was a fun survey. Really made me think on the moral implications of social situations
I thought the study was interesting and I enjoyed it.
The wording is a little weird for this project when it comes to what you're rating the decisions as
This was actually an interesting study. Many are rather boring, but I don't know why, exactly, but this one was more interesting than most.
Understanding the terms "obligatory" and particularly "forbidden" was a bit confusing.
Interesting and engaging study, thank you
Very interesting survey! Very thought provoking...
No, this was a neat survey.
